This paper deals with a machine learning technique (Boolean matrix factorization) and proposes a method to control false discoveries. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves probability theory and statistical analysis, which could place it in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the usage of the false discovery rate, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
